    {
      "instruction": "<p>Slice the<strong> Greek cheese</strong> in half</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped dill</strong> to a shallow bowl with the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and 3 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[6 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Season with a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong> and give everything a good mix up – this is your<strong> herby marinade</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>halved Greek cheese</strong> to the bowl, ensuring the Greek cheese is fully coated in the marinade, set aside until later</p>",
